title: Hurricane Nicole Causes Four Deaths, Forces Evacuation of Unsteady Buildings
description: The storm was especially hard on Volusia County, northeast of Orlando, where officials said that inspectors had deemed 24 hotels and condominiums unsafe.
dc:creator: Eric Adelson, Abigail Geiger, Remy Tumin and Patricia Mazzei

media:content.media:credit: Zack Wittman for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: A swimming pool was split in half after storm surge from Hurricane Nicole collapsed the sea wall in Wilbur-by-the-Sea, Fla., on Thursday.
